<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The MHD_PANIC macro expands to do { mhd_panic(...); BUILTIN_NOT_REACHED; } while (0). If mhd_panic does not return (as intended for a panic/abort routine), the BUILTIN_NOT_REACHED token (typically a __builtin_unreachable or similar) and any code following the macro in the same branch can never be reached. That introduces unreachable code paths (the BUILTIN_NOT_REACHED statement itself and the subsequent statements in that execution path), which violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.1.
</scenario>
